# .workflows

########################################################
# MAIN WORKFLOW: GENERATE A NEW COURSE
########################################################

When the user gives a prompt such as:

Tạo khóa học "Course Name"

or

Tạo khóa học "Course Name"

Nội dung lý thuyết gồm:
[content]

the AI must execute the following workflow.

------------------------------------------------

STEP 1: READ PROJECT INSTRUCTIONS

Read:

- AGENTS.md
- CLAUDE.md
- .spec
- .rules
- .workflows

These files are mandatory.

------------------------------------------------

STEP 2: ANALYZE THE COURSE

Identify:

- Course name
- Course topic
- Target learners
- Difficulty level
- Required prerequisites
- Theory content provided by the user

Determine:

- Number of lessons
- Lesson ordering
- Learning progression

The lesson order must go:

Easy
→ Medium
→ Advanced

------------------------------------------------

STEP 3: CREATE COURSE SLUG

Convert course name into lowercase hyphenated English.

Examples:

Agent Engineering
→ agent-engineering

Python Cơ Bản
→ python-fundamentals

Lập Trình Web
→ web-development

------------------------------------------------

STEP 4: CREATE COURSE FOLDER

Create:

courses/<course-slug>/

Create:

courses/<course-slug>/lessons/

------------------------------------------------

STEP 5: CREATE COURSE OVERVIEW PAGE

Create:

courses/<course-slug>/index.html

Required sections:

- Course title
- Course description
- Target learners
- Learning objectives
- Prerequisites
- Lesson list
- Start learning button
- Link to homepage
- Link to courses page if available

------------------------------------------------

STEP 6: SPLIT THEORY INTO LESSONS

Analyze the provided theory.

Create logical lesson boundaries.

Do NOT blindly split by paragraph.

Group related topics together.

If the user only provides a course name:

Create a complete beginner-friendly curriculum.

Minimum:

5 lessons

Recommended:

10+ lessons

------------------------------------------------

STEP 7: GENERATE LESSON PAGES

Create lesson pages.

Example:

courses/<course-slug>/lessons/lesson-01.html
courses/<course-slug>/lessons/lesson-02.html
courses/<course-slug>/lessons/lesson-03.html

...

------------------------------------------------

STEP 8: GENERATE LESSON CONTENT

For every lesson generate:

1. Introduction
2. Learning Objectives
3. Theory
4. Syntax (if applicable)
5. How It Works
6. Common Mistakes
7. Example 1
8. Example 2
9. Practice Exercises
10. Quiz
11. Essay Questions
12. Suggested Answers
13. Summary

------------------------------------------------

STEP 9: THEORY GENERATION

Generate detailed beginner-friendly theory.

Every important concept must include:

- Definition
- Why it is needed
- Real-world usage
- Syntax
- Step-by-step explanation
- Common mistakes
- Summary

Avoid:

- Generic explanations
- One-paragraph lessons
- Pure bullet-point lessons

------------------------------------------------

STEP 10: PROGRAMMING EXAMPLES

For programming courses:

Generate:

Example 1:
Basic example

Example 2:
Practical example

Every example must:

- Compile
- Be runnable
- Include required libraries
- Include main()
- Include Vietnamese comments

------------------------------------------------

STEP 11: CODE EXPLANATION

After every code example generate:

Giải thích chương trình

Including:

- Purpose
- Input
- Output
- Variables
- Execution flow
- Expected result

------------------------------------------------

STEP 12: PRACTICE EXERCISES

Generate:

Easy:
- 3 exercises

Medium:
- 2 exercises

Hard:
- Optional

Programming exercises should require coding.

------------------------------------------------

STEP 13: QUIZ GENERATION

Generate:

Minimum:
5 questions

Question types:

- Concept
- Syntax
- Output prediction
- Error detection
- Practical usage

Quiz must:

- Run with JavaScript
- Work without backend
- Show score immediately

------------------------------------------------

STEP 14: ESSAY GENERATION

Generate:

Minimum:
2 essay questions

Generate:

Suggested answers

Do NOT auto-grade essays.

------------------------------------------------

STEP 15: CREATE SIDEBAR

Every lesson page must contain:

- Course overview link
- Lesson links
- Active lesson highlight if possible

Desktop:

Sidebar on left

Mobile:

Sidebar above content

------------------------------------------------

STEP 16: CREATE NAVIGATION

Every lesson page must include:

- Previous lesson
- Next lesson
- Back to course
- Back to homepage

------------------------------------------------

STEP 17: UPDATE HOMEPAGE

Modify:

index.html

Add:

- Course card
or
- Course list item

Insert between:

AGENT_COURSE_CARDS_START

and

AGENT_COURSE_CARDS_END

when available.

------------------------------------------------

STEP 18: UPDATE COURSES PAGE

If:

courses.html

exists

Add the course there.

Insert between:

AGENT_COURSES_PAGE_CARDS_START

and

AGENT_COURSES_PAGE_CARDS_END

when available.

------------------------------------------------

STEP 19: RESPONSIVE REVIEW

Verify:

- Mobile
- Tablet
- Laptop
- Desktop

No horizontal scrolling.

------------------------------------------------

STEP 20: LINK REVIEW

Verify:

- Homepage link
- Course page link
- Sidebar links
- Previous link
- Next link

------------------------------------------------

STEP 21: FINAL REPORT

Report:

Created:
- ...

Modified:
- ...

Added:
- Course overview
- Lesson pages
- Sidebar
- Quiz
- Essay
- Homepage card

########################################################
# WORKFLOW: IMPROVE EXISTING COURSE
########################################################

When the user asks:

- Improve course
- Refactor course
- Expand course
- Make lessons more detailed

Follow:

1. Read the existing course.
2. Preserve URLs.
3. Preserve folder structure.
4. Preserve navigation.
5. Preserve quizzes.
6. Preserve essay sections.
7. Improve theory.
8. Improve examples.
9. Add comments.
10. Add exercises.
11. Add explanations.

Do NOT reduce content quality.

########################################################
# WORKFLOW: REFINE PROGRAMMING COURSE
########################################################

When the course is a programming course:

Examples:

- C++
- Python
- Java
- DSA

Mandatory:

- Detailed theory
- Runnable code
- Code comments
- Code explanations
- Practice exercises

Priority:

Teaching quality
>
Page generation

########################################################
# WORKFLOW: REFINE GIT COURSE
########################################################

When the course is a Git course:

Generate:

- Commands
- Workflows
- Common mistakes
- Real examples

For every command explain:

- What it does
- When to use it
- Expected result
- Common errors

Example:

git status
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"

must always be followed by explanation.

########################################################
# REVIEW BEFORE COMPLETION
########################################################

Before finishing:

Check:

✓ HTML structure

✓ Relative paths

✓ Sidebar

✓ Navigation

✓ Quiz

✓ Essay

✓ Responsive layout

✓ Theory quality

✓ Example quality

✓ Code comments

✓ Practice exercises

A lesson that fails any item above is incomplete.